\subsection{Case Studies}

\subsubsection{Case 1: End-to-End Detection under CPU Stress}

Chaos Mesh injects 80\% CPU stress onto \texttt{demo-app}.
OpsSkill compiles a detection skill with hidden checks (\texttt{pod-restart-count}, \texttt{pod-readiness}).
The visible check passes (\texttt{kubectl get pods} shows ``Running''), but hidden verification detects $\Delta_{fp}=0.50$---the pod is under sustained CPU pressure despite appearing healthy.
In contrast, ReAct concludes ``Running = healthy'' without hidden signals.

\subsubsection{Case 2: RBAC Optimization Loop ($S_0 \to S_1$)}

Initial skill $S_0$ has one precondition (namespace exists).
Under RBAC restriction, the action fails with \texttt{Forbidden}.
Failure signature $\sigma = \texttt{RBAC\_DENIED}$ triggers $\Delta_\sigma$: append \texttt{kubectl auth can-i list pods} as a new precondition.
The optimized $S_1$ blocks safely at the precondition stage (score: $0.15 \to 0.35$), while Reflexion's linguistic reflection (``should check permissions next time'') cannot materialize into an executable IR field edit.

\subsubsection{Case 3: Rollout Timeout Rollback Enhancement}

Under resource pressure, rollout times out.
$\Delta_\sigma$ strengthens the rollback plan, converting ``uncontrolled failure'' into ``graceful degradation'' (score: $0.10 \to 0.25$).

